Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers
NEW DELHI , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Indian newspapers Monday .
The Hindustan Times :
-- Heavy rains which lashed the Indian capital Sunday brought almost the entire city to a standstill , with numerous water-logged roads hindering the flow of traffic .
The Times of India :
-- A retired naval commander was found murdered in his house in south Delhi on Sunday .
The Statesman :
-- More than 100 drug counseling centers all over the country are expected to be hit hard with the Indian Welfare Ministry deciding to suspend annual aid to these centers .
The Economic Times :
-- Asset management companies of leading mutual funds , which have shown poor performance , are sitting on a veritable time-bomb .
